1
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:07,878
-This is an easy one, you love this guy.
-Me.

2
00:00:09,119 --> 00:00:12,395
Come on.
He's an underappreciated genius...

3
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,791
Still think it's me.

4
00:00:15,279 --> 00:00:18,908
It's not you. Now think.
There's a car named after him.

5
00:00:19,079 --> 00:00:21,912
Of course there is.
The Mini Cooper, because it's me.

6
00:00:24,599 --> 00:00:26,317
How about this?

7
00:00:26,640 --> 00:00:28,119
He's a poor man's Sheldon Cooper.

8
00:00:28,279 --> 00:00:29,473
Oh, Tesla.

9
00:00:30,679 --> 00:00:32,397
-Hi.
-Hey, how'd it go?

10
00:00:32,560 --> 00:00:36,030
Not fun. The doctor shoved
a camera up into my sinuses.

11
00:00:36,199 --> 00:00:39,828
Yeah, I watched. It was like
the scary boat tunnel in Willy Wonka.

12
00:00:41,519 --> 00:00:43,987
-They figure out what's wrong?
-lt's a deviated septum.

13
00:00:44,160 --> 00:00:46,435
The surgery is simple.
He's gonna do it next week.

14
00:00:46,799 --> 00:00:48,278
Why would you have surgery?

15
00:00:48,440 --> 00:00:49,873
Because I can't breathe.

16
00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:52,395
And I snore, I get sinus infections....

17
00:00:52,560 --> 00:00:54,790
Back off, he's all mine.

18
00:00:54,959 --> 00:00:58,713
You don't have a life-threatening condition.
Why would you take the risk of surgery?

19
00:00:58,880 --> 00:01:02,509
Sheldon, it's a routine procedure.
I've heard you complain about his snoring.

20
00:01:02,679 --> 00:01:06,194
Yes, for the first five or six years,
but I've gotten used to it.

21
00:01:06,639 --> 00:01:08,118
It helps me sleep.

22
00:01:08,280 --> 00:01:10,669
He's like my mucus-powered
white-noise machine.

23
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:15,033
Sheldon, I'm gonna get the surgery.
It's no big deal, end of story.

24
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,430
-Very well, I'm done talking about it.
-Thank you.

25
00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:19,909
-I believe it was your turn in the game.
-Okay.

26
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:25,309
Let's see. Oh, this person
is most famous...

27
00:01:25,479 --> 00:01:29,472
...for never having gotten his nose
mutilated with elective surgery...

28
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:31,835
...and never living his life
in the shadows...

29
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,833
...as a hideous disfigured freak.

30
00:01:35,039 --> 00:01:36,995
I think you could give a better clue.

31
00:01:37,160 --> 00:01:41,119
I don't. I'm not even sure
if that's a person or a typo.

32
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:08,635
[SNORING]

33
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:21,671
Okay, why?

34
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:24,669
I'm listening to you snore.

35
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:27,229
I'm wondering how
I'll ever sleep without it.

36
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:30,873
If it helps you sleep,
then why are you sitting here...

37
00:02:31,040 --> 00:02:33,838
...staring at me
like the albino boogeyman?

38
00:02:35,519 --> 00:02:36,952
Really, Leonard, insults?

39
00:02:37,119 --> 00:02:40,828
After I spent two hours in your closet
waiting for you to fall asleep?

40
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:46,397
-What's your problem?
-If the surgery is successful...

41
00:02:46,559 --> 00:02:48,151
...the snoring is gone.

42
00:02:48,320 --> 00:02:50,436
And if you die during surgery...

43
00:02:51,799 --> 00:02:53,676
...the snoring is gone.

44
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:58,157
Sounds like either way
I finally get some rest.

45
00:02:58,639 --> 00:03:01,597
l have to be honest with you, Leonard.
I'm truly worried.

46
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:04,354
Okay, I told you,
there's nothing to worry about.

47
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:08,274
I've been doing some research,
and I've learned that 1 in 700,000 people...

48
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:10,431
...die from general anesthesia.

49
00:03:11,079 --> 00:03:17,678
Buddy, do you realize that also means
699,999 people don't die?

50
00:03:19,039 --> 00:03:20,233
I suppose that's true.

51
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:25,192
You're such a glass half-full kind of guy.

52
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:28,476
I'm going to miss that.

53
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:34,312
Oh, so my parents' 40th anniversary
is coming up...

54
00:03:34,480 --> 00:03:36,357
...and I can't think of a thing to get.

55
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:41,197
Damn. Can you imagine being married
to someone for 40 years?

56
00:03:44,080 --> 00:03:45,798
Not anymore.

57
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:52,270
Anyway, any ideas on a gift?

58
00:03:52,559 --> 00:03:54,356
What are some of the things they like?

59
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:56,711
They liked going to
the Mumbai Symphony...

60
00:03:56,879 --> 00:03:58,790
...but last year, my mom thought
they were phoning it in.

61
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:02,829
Then my dad said, based on their love life,
she should know about phoning it in.

62
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,317
-He said that?
-They weren't speaking...

63
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:08,152
...so he had a servant say it to her.

64
00:04:09,079 --> 00:04:11,115
Oh, maybe I could make a gift for them.

65
00:04:11,279 --> 00:04:15,557
I know how much you guys love
the coasters I made for you.

66
00:04:17,239 --> 00:04:19,036
They're yours in the divorce.

67
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,153
Hey, what are you working on?

68
00:04:25,319 --> 00:04:27,833
Remember when I said
if you went through with surgery...

69
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,309
...there was a1 in 700,000
chance of dying?

70
00:04:30,479 --> 00:04:31,468
[SIGHS]

71
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:34,278
-Yeah.
-Well, I've been crunching the numbers...

72
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:37,273
...and so far, I've gotten
your probability of death...

73
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:41,194
...all the way to a sphincter-tightening
1 in 300.

74
00:04:43,359 --> 00:04:46,908
Great timing.
My "check sphincter" light just went on.

75
00:04:47,799 --> 00:04:50,029
Leonard, what if you have
an allergic reaction...

76
00:04:50,199 --> 00:04:53,111
-...to the surgeon's latex gloves?
-l'm not allergic to latex.

77
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:56,278
Then why don't you wear the gloves
I bought to do the dishes?

78
00:04:56,440 --> 00:04:59,591
For the same reason
I don't wear the apron or the hairnet.

79
00:05:00,039 --> 00:05:02,394
Fine. What about epilepsy?

80
00:05:02,560 --> 00:05:04,152
I don't have epilepsy either.

81
00:05:04,319 --> 00:05:06,469
No, you don't,
but the surgeon might. Hm?

82
00:05:06,799 --> 00:05:09,677
And your carotid artery
is just one shaky scalpel away...

83
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:13,230
...from becoming the dancing fountain
at Disneyland.

84
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:16,472
Sheldon, do you realize
that driving is riskier than surgery?

85
00:05:16,639 --> 00:05:19,597
I do. I have the drive
to the hospital right here.

86
00:05:20,039 --> 00:05:23,349
That is, if you make it to the car
without falling down the stairs.

87
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:26,239
And don't expect me to carry you,
I do that enough in life.

88
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:30,318
Buddy, I get that you're worried about me,
and I appreciate that...

89
00:05:30,479 --> 00:05:32,071
...but I'm not going to die.

90
00:05:32,239 --> 00:05:33,638
You don't know that.

91
00:05:33,799 --> 00:05:36,757
I do know that it won't be
from an asteroid strike.

92
00:05:38,119 --> 00:05:39,472
You know who else said that?

93
00:05:39,639 --> 00:05:43,314
Every cocky 1'. Rex currently swimming
around in the gas tank of your car.

94
00:05:44,479 --> 00:05:47,312
If there was an asteroid strike,
wouldn't you die too?

95
00:05:47,479 --> 00:05:50,949
I don't know. I'm smart and scrappy.
I think I'd find a way.

96
00:05:53,079 --> 00:05:55,991
Tell you what, the surgery's not for a week.
I'll think about it.

97
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:58,515
Thank you.
And while you're thinking about it...

98
00:05:58,679 --> 00:06:01,557
...if you have the surgery in Nicaragua
during monsoon season...

99
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,358
...I can guarantee your death.

100
00:06:09,120 --> 00:06:11,190
Yes. Okay.

101
00:06:11,359 --> 00:06:13,156
I understand.

102
00:06:13,319 --> 00:06:15,992
Of course, yes. I'll call you tomorrow.

103
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:17,434
Bye.

104
00:06:17,959 --> 00:06:20,792
So I found this fencing school
in Burbank...

105
00:06:20,959 --> 00:06:24,076
...that has a Jedi class.

106
00:06:25,239 --> 00:06:28,675
If you're cool being the only adults there,
they said they are.

107
00:06:29,839 --> 00:06:31,397
Dude, my parents just split up.

108
00:06:31,559 --> 00:06:34,073
-What?
-Uh, that was my dad on the phone.

109
00:06:34,239 --> 00:06:35,797
He moved out.

110
00:06:36,160 --> 00:06:39,311
Oh, my God. I'm sorry.

111
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:41,596
If you're not up to it,
we don't have to go out.

112
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:44,035
-We can just hang here.
-No, it's fine.

113
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:47,510
It's not that big a deal.
As long as they're happy, I'm happy.

114
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,830
And when I get to see them
for the holidays...

115
00:06:49,999 --> 00:06:53,196
...I get to celebrate Diwali twice,
one at each house.

116
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:57,914
That's double the Diwali.

117
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:00,831
-You sure you're okay?
-l'm okay.

118
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,797
-You don't look okay.
-How can I be okay?

119
00:07:02,959 --> 00:07:04,278
I come from a broken home.

120
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:09,989
Doctor said I should be
out of surgery by 10.

121
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:15,473
Okay. And Sheldon really believes
we're at a public swimming pool?

122
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:19,038
He was so busy figuring out
how many parts per million of urine...

123
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:22,272
...we'd be floating around in,
he didn't even question it.

124
00:07:22,679 --> 00:07:25,432
Eighteen parts per million.

125
00:07:26,720 --> 00:07:28,870
And he's still doing it.

126
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:31,390
Don't worry about it.
I'm happy to take you to work.

127
00:07:31,559 --> 00:07:32,787
Well, thank you.

128
00:07:32,959 --> 00:07:36,156
And Leonard never lets me
have French toast sticks in the car.

129
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:38,197
I can't have syrupy fingers...

130
00:07:38,359 --> 00:07:41,669
...but he can do the backstroke
in a toilet bowl.

131
00:07:42,799 --> 00:07:44,357
It's nice they're getting exercise.

132
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:47,948
Although, now that I think about it...

133
00:07:48,119 --> 00:07:52,078
...Leonard would never go swimming
in public without his swim shirt.

134
00:07:53,239 --> 00:07:56,470
-l'm sure he brought it.
-No, but last year at Magic Mountain...

135
00:07:56,639 --> 00:08:00,393
...he got such a bad sunburn,
we had to cut him out of it.

136
00:08:01,559 --> 00:08:03,754
He probably got a new one.
Finish your breakfast.

137
00:08:03,919 --> 00:08:07,992
There's an entire section of my dashboard
that doesn't have any syrup on it.

138
00:08:08,879 --> 00:08:10,915
You're acting odd. Why?

139
00:08:11,799 --> 00:08:13,835
I'm odd all the time, everyone knows that.

140
00:08:14,639 --> 00:08:18,109
Just last night I tried to see how many
fava beans I could fit in my mouth.

141
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:21,790
-Tell me the truth.
-Twenty-eight.

142
00:08:22,839 --> 00:08:25,990
-Come on.
-Fifty-six.

143
00:08:26,160 --> 00:08:29,550
Amy. What's going on?

144
00:08:29,720 --> 00:08:31,073
All right.

145
00:08:31,519 --> 00:08:33,828
Don't get upset...

146
00:08:33,999 --> 00:08:36,433
...but an earlier appointment
opened up for Leonard...

147
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,989
...and he's getting the surgery right now.

148
00:08:42,759 --> 00:08:44,351


149
00:08:49,839 --> 00:08:51,067
Take me to Leonard.

150
00:08:51,480 --> 00:08:54,631
-Just go to work. He'll be fine.
-Amy, he's my best friend.

151
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:57,234
And if you don't take me,
I'm going there anyway.

152
00:08:58,160 --> 00:08:59,912
Fine.

153
00:09:00,359 --> 00:09:04,034
-lt's sweet that you care about him so much.
-I do.

154
00:09:04,199 --> 00:09:06,713
I couldn't forgive myself
if something happened to him...

155
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:09,712
...and I wasn't at his bedside to say,
"I told you so."

156
00:09:14,719 --> 00:09:17,392
[WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PA]

157
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:25,714
-Hello.
-We had a really nice swim.

158
00:09:25,879 --> 00:09:26,914
Oh, stop it.

159
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:31,318
I assume this medical center's
treated the bums on your bottom...

160
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,710
...from the recent pants fire.

161
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:38,237
-Because I'm a liar, liar?
-That's for the fire marshal to determine.

162
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:43,040
-You had to tell him?
-He wore me down.

163
00:09:43,199 --> 00:09:46,953
And I was distracted.
He has on extra baby powder today.

164
00:09:48,079 --> 00:09:50,195
-Is he okay?
-He's still in surgery.

165
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,509
[SHELDON SIGHS]

166
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:55,389
-Very well.
-He's gonna be all right.

167
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:57,755
That is sticky.

168
00:09:59,759 --> 00:10:02,319
Let's talk about something
other than the surgery.

169
00:10:02,480 --> 00:10:05,517
That's a good idea.
Penny, did you and Leonard...

170
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:07,796
...ever discuss funeral arrangements?

171
00:10:09,360 --> 00:10:11,828
I think she meant something
a little happier.

172
00:10:12,959 --> 00:10:16,076
I suppose we can try
to make it a celebration...

173
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,117
...but he died so young.

174
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:21,909
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

175
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,433
-Knock, knock.
-Hi.

176
00:10:23,599 --> 00:10:28,514
-Hey, what brings you guys by?
-Oh, muffin much.

177
00:10:29,999 --> 00:10:32,194
Told you, not funny.

178
00:10:32,519 --> 00:10:37,639
Well, he's just not laughing
because he's feeling blueberry.

179
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:40,992
Tough crowd.

180
00:10:42,879 --> 00:10:46,394
-l'm sorry. This is very sweet, thanks.
-So how you doing?

181
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:49,836
Better. I guess the news just hit me
a lot harder than I expected.

182
00:10:49,999 --> 00:10:53,594
Well, of course. I would be devastated
if my parents split up.

183
00:10:53,760 --> 00:10:56,797
Why? Your father barely speaks
to your mother. Heh.

184
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:59,952
Well, at least he stuck around.
Not like your dad, who just took off.

185
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:02,914
As you can see,
we're here to cheer you up.

186
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:07,317
Sorry, Raj. Do you have any sense
of what happened with your folks?

187
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:11,157
I think over time,
they started to resent each other.

188
00:11:11,319 --> 00:11:14,197
Instead of talking about things,
they kept it bottled up...

189
00:11:14,359 --> 00:11:16,429
...and the hate just grew.

190
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:19,512
It's a shame they spent
all that time unhappy...

191
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:24,390
...but sometimes,
there's muffin you can do about it.

192
00:11:25,840 --> 00:11:27,273
You get it, right?

193
00:11:31,480 --> 00:11:33,198
Well, it's nice you got him that.

194
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,839
Oh, this isn't for Leonard. No.

195
00:11:34,999 --> 00:11:37,115
Amy bought it for me.

196
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:42,358
He stubbed his toe on the revolving door
on the way in.

197
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:44,995
You know those confounded things
make me dizzy.

198
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:48,038
Who told you to keep going around?

199
00:11:48,199 --> 00:11:51,555
There was a large plant in the lobby.
It kept looking like the outside.

200
00:11:53,199 --> 00:11:55,235
When Leonard comes out,
he's not gonna feel great...

201
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,231
...so please don't give him a hard time.

202
00:11:57,399 --> 00:11:58,991
Penny has a good point.

203
00:11:59,159 --> 00:12:02,231
This is like the man in the supermarket
with the goiter on his neck.

204
00:12:02,399 --> 00:12:05,357
Whatever you're thinking,
just keep it to yourself.

205
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,720
It was like a grapefruit.

206
00:12:09,079 --> 00:12:10,307
And I'm sure he knew that...

207
00:12:10,479 --> 00:12:13,391
...before you held a grapefruit
up next to it.

208
00:12:13,839 --> 00:12:15,397
Well, I'm not making any promises.

209
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:18,120
Not only did Leonard take
what I feel is an unnecessary risk...

210
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:20,430
-...he deceived me.
-The reason he deceived you...

211
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:24,036
-...is you were a pain in the ass.
-The reason I was being a pain in the B...

212
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:26,475
...is because I was worried
and no one else was.

213
00:12:26,639 --> 00:12:30,234
-Really? You won't even say A?
-You bet your sweet B I won't.

214
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:34,116
Obviously I care about Leonard. I'm
gonna spend the rest of my life with him.

215
00:12:34,280 --> 00:12:35,759
And I'm not?

216
00:12:36,719 --> 00:12:38,550
[RUMBLING]

217
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:42,999
-lt's an earthquake. I knew it.
-Sheldon, it was just a little tremor.

218
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:45,549
A little tremor that turns
routine sinus surgery...

219
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:48,109
...into a frontal lobotomy.

220
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,077
Oh, I don't care for this at all.

221
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:55,157
I need to see he's okay.

222
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:58,109
-Sheldon, you can't go back there.
SHELDON: Try and stop me.

223
00:12:58,280 --> 00:12:59,554
[THUDS]

224
00:13:01,039 --> 00:13:04,668
AMY: Are you okay?
SHELDON: Why didn't you stop me?

225
00:13:07,839 --> 00:13:09,113
Can I tell you something?

226
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,278
This whole thing with Raj's parents...

227
00:13:11,439 --> 00:13:13,828
...just got me a little worried about us.

228
00:13:13,999 --> 00:13:16,229
What are you talking about? We're fine.

229
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:20,109
And Raj's parents probably split up
because of Raj.

230
00:13:20,719 --> 00:13:21,708
What?

231
00:13:21,879 --> 00:13:24,473
They always say the children
aren't to blame, but....

232
00:13:24,639 --> 00:13:26,675
Heh, come on.

233
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:32,918
I'm notjoking, Howie.
You heard what he said about his parents.

234
00:13:33,080 --> 00:13:35,230
It was the little things
they kept bottled up.

235
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:37,311
I don't want that to happen to us.

236
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,392
How can I convince you it won't?

237
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:42,836
Well, is there anything about me
you're keeping inside?

238
00:13:42,999 --> 00:13:46,389
Heh. I'm not answering that. It's a trap.

239
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:50,952
So there are things you don't like.

240
00:13:51,759 --> 00:13:53,590
And here I am in the trap.

241
00:13:55,719 --> 00:13:59,155
You just keep talking,
I'm gonna chew my leg off.

242
00:13:59,999 --> 00:14:03,116
Just tell me one thing that bothers you
and I promise I won't get mad.

243
00:14:03,839 --> 00:14:05,955
Okay. The truth is...

244
00:14:06,120 --> 00:14:10,477
...sometimes you're too beautiful.

245
00:14:12,520 --> 00:14:13,953
Howie, be serious.

246
00:14:14,319 --> 00:14:15,752
Okay, okay.

247
00:14:15,920 --> 00:14:20,436
I really don't like how your wings
poke me when we sleep...

248
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,670
...because you're an angel.

249
00:14:24,759 --> 00:14:27,398
Okay, fine. Maybe it was a bad idea.

250
00:14:27,560 --> 00:14:31,599
I just don't think the secret to a happy
marriage is to criticize each other.

251
00:14:31,759 --> 00:14:35,718
Although, there are ways
to improve our communication.

252
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:38,633
One thing I learned
when l was in couples therapy was--

253
00:14:38,800 --> 00:14:41,758
-Who were you in couples therapy with?
-Not important.

254
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:45,429
-Was it your mom?
-Not important.

255
00:14:46,319 --> 00:14:47,957
It was your mom.

256
00:14:49,159 --> 00:14:51,150
Anyway, the therapist
had us tell each other...

257
00:14:51,319 --> 00:14:53,594
...what we loved about one another.

258
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:56,879
Oh, that's so sweet. I wanna do that.

259
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,792
Okay.

260
00:14:58,960 --> 00:15:02,919
Okay. Um, I love that you make me laugh.

261
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,469
Thank you.

262
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:09,270
And I love that you're strong
and independent.

263
00:15:09,439 --> 00:15:12,237
And yet, I still love
when you hold a door for me.

264
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:15,437
I love that I'm kind of a slob
around here...

265
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:18,637
...and, heh-heh, you're okay with that.

266
00:15:21,879 --> 00:15:23,676
Uh-huh.

267
00:15:24,879 --> 00:15:29,111
And I love that I work and do
all the cleaning and you're okay with that.

268
00:15:30,799 --> 00:15:33,313
See, I am. Isn't this great?

269
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:39,393
Come on, smile.
This is gonna be my Christmas card.

270
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:46,915
[IN NASALLY VOICE]
You know, this is all your fault.

271
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:49,994
[IN NASALLY VOICE]
How is it my fault?

272
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:52,758
I told you not to get the surgery.

273
00:15:53,399 --> 00:15:56,596
Okay, first of all, the surgery
was a success.

274
00:15:56,759 --> 00:15:58,397
Secondly, I didn't want you there.

275
00:15:59,800 --> 00:16:03,793
Wow. I don't know which hurts worse,
my nose or my heart.

276
00:16:05,280 --> 00:16:06,679
I'm done speaking to you.

277
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:09,195
Don't be like that.
You two need to talk this out.

278
00:16:09,360 --> 00:16:11,555
Yeah, because you sound really funny.

279
00:16:11,719 --> 00:16:12,947
[PENNY LAUGHING]

280
00:16:14,240 --> 00:16:16,549
I'm sorry I didn't tell you
about the surgery...

281
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,517
...but you were worried about nothing.

282
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:20,318
Oh, you're hardly out of the woods.

283
00:16:20,479 --> 00:16:23,551
You still run the risk of infection,
a blood clot...

284
00:16:23,719 --> 00:16:28,190
...the possibility that an inattentive surgeon
let a barn spider lay eggs in your nose.

285
00:16:30,439 --> 00:16:33,272
The minute you sneeze web,
I'm moving out.

286
00:16:33,639 --> 00:16:37,996
I never thought I'd say these words,
but come on, nose spider!

287
00:16:39,120 --> 00:16:41,554
You were so panicked
Leonard was gonna die...

288
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:44,678
-...you'll never leave him.
-Sheldon will move out eventually.

289
00:16:44,840 --> 00:16:46,831
Yeah, once he figures out
how to work a door.

290
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:51,956
l was not panicked.
And I am not overly attached to Leonard.

291
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:54,873
You were so worried that you smashed
your face trying to check on me.

292
00:16:55,039 --> 00:16:57,553
You love me.

293
00:16:58,360 --> 00:17:02,194
Tell me those aren't the words
of a man with a spider eating his brain.

294
00:17:03,399 --> 00:17:04,832
Amy, you're a neuroscientist.

295
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:07,309
Crack his skull open,
spray some Raid in there.

296
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:12,196
I love that you take pride in your looks.

297
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:14,119
Even when l have to pee...

298
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:17,192
...and you're in there
spending an hour on your hair.

299
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:21,430
I love that you're too good to pee
in the kitchen sink.

300
00:17:22,639 --> 00:17:24,470
I love that you have
the confidence to speak...

301
00:17:24,640 --> 00:17:27,359
...even without giving it
an ounce of thought.

302
00:17:28,959 --> 00:17:30,870
I love how your hair
is always on the soap.

303
00:17:31,040 --> 00:17:33,679
It's like washing myself with a hamster.

304
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:35,229
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

305
00:17:35,400 --> 00:17:38,676
Hey, guys. Sorry I am so late.

306
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:40,910
l was on the phone with my mother.

307
00:17:41,079 --> 00:17:42,797
-How is she?
-Pretty good.

308
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:44,916
She bought the book Eat, Pray, Love...

309
00:17:45,079 --> 00:17:47,991
...and used it to set
my father's Mercedes on fire.

310
00:17:50,159 --> 00:17:53,117
So, what's up with you guys?

311
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:55,868
We're just saying all the things
we love about each other.

312
00:17:56,039 --> 00:17:58,428
Oh, like you and I did at couples therapy.

313
00:18:07,520 --> 00:18:10,637
-What'd you get?
-Oh, I ordered it before your surgery.

314
00:18:11,159 --> 00:18:13,957
It's the um I was going to put you in.

315
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:17,675
Okay, that's morbid. Send it back.

316
00:18:17,839 --> 00:18:21,548
I can't send it back. I had it engraved.

317
00:18:22,279 --> 00:18:25,112
"Here lie the ashes of Leonard Hofstadter.

318
00:18:25,279 --> 00:18:29,192
He thought he was right,
but his roommate knew better."

319
00:18:30,279 --> 00:18:31,268
[LEONARD CHUCKLES]

320
00:18:31,440 --> 00:18:34,512
That's funny.
Boy, I'm gonna miss these painkillers.

321
00:18:36,199 --> 00:18:37,917
Hey, why did you get two?

322
00:18:38,559 --> 00:18:40,789
-"l'm with stupid."
-Oh, that one's mine.

323
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:10,111
